## Section 1 – Definitions

a. Adapted Material means material subject to Copyright and Similar
Rights that is derived from or based upon the Licensed Material.

b. Copyright and Similar Rights means copyright and/or similar rights
closely related to copyright.

c. Effective Technological Measures means those measures that, in the
absence of proper authority, may not be circumvented under laws
fulfilling obligations under Article 11 of the WIPO Copyright Treaty.

d. Licensed Material means the artistic or literary work, database, or
other material to which the Licensor applied this Public License.

e. Licensed Rights means the rights granted to You subject to the terms
and conditions of this Public License.

f. Licensor means the individual(s) or entity(ies) granting rights
under this Public License.

g. NonCommercial means not primarily intended for or directed towards
commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

h. Share means to provide material to the public by any means or
process that requires permission under the Licensed Rights.

i. You means the individual or entity exercising the Licensed Rights.

